The 2010 running of the '''[[Shelby American]]''' was the third race of the 2010 NASCAR [[Sprint Cup Series]] season at [[Las Vegas Motor Speedway]] in Las Vegas, Nevada. The race honored the 10 years of Carrol Shelby Inc. with the track. It started at 3 p.m. EST on February 28, 2010. The race length was 276 laps or 400.5 miles. The Shelby American was televised on FOX and was also broadcast on MRN radio. All practice sessions including Happy Hour was televised on SPEED. In first practice the top five fastest drivers were  [[Juan Pablo Montoya]], [[Sam Hornish Jr.]],  [[Jimmie Johnson]], [[Mark Martin]], [[Jeff Gordon]]. <ref>[http://www.nascar.com/races/cup/2010/3/data/practice1_speeds.html Practice results]</ref >During qualifying [[Kurt Busch]] ran the fastest lap with the speed of 188.719 and a time of 28.614 to be on the pole position<ref>[http://www.nascar.com/races/cup/2010/3/data/lineup.html Start lineup]</ref> while [[Casey Mears]] and [[Terry Cook]] failed to qualify. In the second practice for the Shelby American [[Kyle Busch]], [[Greg Biffle]], Kurt Busch, [[David Reutimann]], and [[Clint Bowyer]] were the fastest.<ref>[http://www.nascar.com/races/cup/2010/3/data/practice2_speeds.html Practice 2 speeds]</ref> In happy hour Clint Bowyer, Juan Pablo Montoya, Mark Martin, Jimmie Johnson, and [[Marcos Ambrose]] were the fastest<ref>[http://www.nascar.com/races/cup/2010/3/data/practice3_speeds.html Happy Hour Speeds]</ref>, but unlike the first two practices happy hour had one caution with [[Dale Earnhardt Jr.]] spinning onto pit road.<ref>[http://www.nascar.com/video/cup/2010/preview/practice/02/27/cup_las_high_practice_junior.nascar/index.html Dale Earnhardt Jr.]</ref>The winner of the 2010 Shelby American was Jimmie Johnson.<ref>[http://www.nascar.com/races/cup/2010/3/data/results_unofficial.html Unofficial results]</ref>

==Race summary==
Jimmie Johnson won the Shelby American at Las Vegas Motor Speedway, beating Kevin Harvick to the checkered flag by 1.874 seconds. Jeff Gordon, Mark Martin and Matt Kenseth round out the top 5 in the running order.<ref>[http://www.nascar.com/races/cup/2010/3/data/results_unofficial.html Unofficial results]</ref> Jimmie Johnson pushed the #48 Chevrolet to an average speed of 141.414 mph and led 18 of the race's 267 laps. The race ran 2:52:52 and saw 20 lead changes. Due to 7 yellow flags, the race spent 29 laps under caution.<ref>[http://msn.foxsports.com/nascar/cup/raceTrax?gameId=20100228028&state=RACE# Lap-By-Lap]</ref>

